{"id":10705,"date":"2023-01-10T12:33:15","date_gmt":"2023-01-10T12:33:15","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/?p=10705"},"modified":"2023-03-13T10:13:08","modified_gmt":"2023-03-13T10:13:08","slug":"the-steps-to-manage-agile-software-delivery-plans-across-teams","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2023\/01\/10\/the-steps-to-manage-agile-software-delivery-plans-across-teams\/","title":{"rendered":"The steps to manage Agile software delivery plans across teams."},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>The delivery plan shows the scheduled work items by sprint of selected teams against a calendar view, we use it to ensure that our teams are aligned with our organizational goals.<br>We are going to use an Azure DevOps Demo Generator Template project which is: Manage Agile Software delivery plans across teams. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"550\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/3-select-template-1024x550.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10709\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/3-select-template-1024x550.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/3-select-template-300x161.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/3-select-template-768x413.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/3-select-template-1536x825.png 1536w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/3-select-template-50x27.png 50w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/3-select-template.png 1603w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">1. <strong>Create the Delivery Plan<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">1. Select the Template and create the project.<br>2. From the Boards of the created project, select Delivery Plans.<br>3. It will show that there are no plans, so let&#8217;s create a new one.<br>4. Click on the New Plan button.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"551\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/7-new-plan-1024x551.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10710\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/7-new-plan-1024x551.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/7-new-plan-300x162.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/7-new-plan-768x413.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/7-new-plan-1536x827.png 1536w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/7-new-plan-50x27.png 50w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/7-new-plan.png 1603w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>5. Type your delivery plan&#8217;s desired name.<br>6. Add teams, I have added two teams (one for the web team and the other for the Engine team).<br>7. Select Backlog for each team (maybe on Epic, Feature, or Backlog Item levels), I have selected Backlog items.<br>8. Click Create.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"553\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/8-delivery-plan-configs-1024x553.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10711\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/8-delivery-plan-configs-1024x553.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/8-delivery-plan-configs-300x162.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/8-delivery-plan-configs-768x415.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/8-delivery-plan-configs-1536x830.png 1536w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/8-delivery-plan-configs-50x27.png 50w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/8-delivery-plan-configs.png 1603w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>2. Add milestone markers.<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>1. From the settings of the delivery plan, select add markers<br>2. To set a marker, open&nbsp;<strong>Markers<\/strong>, specify a date and specify a hexadecimal colour, or choose the colour palette icon to change to a new colour selected by the system.<br>3. To add more markers, choose&nbsp;<strong>+ Add marker<\/strong>. You can add up to 30 markers. The&nbsp;<strong>+ Add marker<\/strong>&nbsp;button becomes disabled after 30 markers have been added.<br>4. Choose <strong>Save<\/strong> when you are done.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"549\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/12-markers-added-1024x549.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10712\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/12-markers-added-1024x549.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/12-markers-added-300x161.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/12-markers-added-768x412.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/12-markers-added-1536x823.png 1536w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/12-markers-added-50x27.png 50w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/12-markers-added.png 1603w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Markers appear on the plan as shown.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"550\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/13-marker-added-1024x550.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10713\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/13-marker-added-1024x550.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/13-marker-added-300x161.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/13-marker-added-768x413.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/13-marker-added-1536x825.png 1536w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/13-marker-added-50x27.png 50w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/13-marker-added.png 1603w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">3. Track dependencies by using Delivery Plans<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>With Delivery Plans, you can track dependencies that have been added to work items.<br>Those cards with a green icon indicate there are no dependency issues. <br>Those cards with a&nbsp;red icon indicate there are issues with one or more dependencies.<br>Dependency issues arise when a predecessor work item is scheduled to finish after a successor work item.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"551\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/16-four-depend-1024x551.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10716\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/16-four-depend-1024x551.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/16-four-depend-300x161.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/16-four-depend-768x413.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/16-four-depend-1536x826.png 1536w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/16-four-depend-50x27.png 50w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/16-four-depend.png 1603w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To view dependency lines for a work item, select the top or bottom of its card. <br>To dismiss the lines select the top or bottom of the card again, or anywhere else within the plan.<br>Dependency lines that have no issues show up as black lines.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"550\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/19-green-arrow-direction-1024x550.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10717\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/19-green-arrow-direction-1024x550.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/19-green-arrow-direction-300x161.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/19-green-arrow-direction-768x413.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/19-green-arrow-direction-1536x825.png 1536w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/19-green-arrow-direction-50x27.png 50w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/19-green-arrow-direction.png 1603w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Dependency lines that have issues, show up with red lines. <br>The issues indicate that the successor work item is scheduled to end before the predecessor work item is completed.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"553\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/18-red-arrow-direction-1024x553.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10718\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/18-red-arrow-direction-1024x553.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/18-red-arrow-direction-300x162.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/18-red-arrow-direction-768x414.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/18-red-arrow-direction-1536x829.png 1536w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/18-red-arrow-direction-50x27.png 50w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/18-red-arrow-direction.png 1603w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After defining all the wrong dependencies, you can fix them by reordering the items to the sprints.<br>After moving items the dependency has been fixed (the colour will be changed from red to green).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"551\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/22-all-are-green-1024x551.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10719\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/22-all-are-green-1024x551.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/22-all-are-green-300x162.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/22-all-are-green-768x413.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/22-all-are-green-1536x827.png 1536w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/22-all-are-green-50x27.png 50w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/22-all-are-green.png 1603w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The delivery plan shows the scheduled work items by sprint &hellip;<\/p>\n<p class=\"read-more\"> <a class=\"ast-button\" href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2023\/01\/10\/the-steps-to-manage-agile-software-delivery-plans-across-teams\/\"> <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">The steps to manage Agile software delivery plans across teams.<\/span> Read More<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":10720,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"d